---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Refund Policy — Miller Trust Guide"
  description="Money-back guarantee. Full refund if your state Medicaid agency rejects the QIT for any reason traceable to following the kit."
>
  <article class="prose-content mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">Last updated 2026-05-20.</p>

    <h2>Money-back guarantee</h2>
    <p>
      If your state's Medicaid agency rejects the Qualified Income Trust for any reason traceable to following this
      kit, we issue a <strong>full refund within one business day</strong> of receiving the agency's stated denial
      reason.
    </p>

    <h2>How to request a refund</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Email <a href="mailto:support@millertrustguide.com">support@millertrustguide.com</a> from the email address used at checkout.</li>
      <li>Include the agency's stated denial reason (a quote or the relevant section of the denial letter is fine — no need to share personal financial details).</li>
      <li>We process the refund to your original payment method. Funds typically appear within 3–5 business days.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Standard refund window</h2>
    <p>
      For any other reason, refund requests submitted within <strong>30 days of purchase</strong> are honored without
      question. After 30 days, contact us — we'd rather hear about a problem than have an unhappy buyer.
    </p>

    <h2>What is not covered</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Denials based on facts unrelated to the QIT itself (asset limit issues, look-back transfers, citizenship verification, etc.).</li>
      <li>Denials caused by deviating from the kit's instructions or using a non-state-published template.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If the denial is borderline, we default to issuing the refund.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p><a href="mailto:support@millertrustguide.com">support@millertrustguide.com</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
